summary.@value: This is a list of all sources that sent in messages to Graylog.

description.@value: This is a list of all sources that sent in messages to Graylog. You can narrow the timerange by zooming in on the message histogram, or you can increase the time range by specifying a broader one in the controls at the top. You can also specify filters to limit the results you are seeing. You can also add additional widgets to this dashboard, or adapt the appearance of existing widgets to suit your needs.

grok_pattern.@value: log_level=%{WORD:log_level} \| log_timestamp=%{TIMESTAMP_ISO8601:log_timestamp} \| log_source=%{NOTSPACE:log_source} \| log_uid=%{NOTSPACE:log_uid} \| log_oec=%{NOTSPACE:log_oec} \| log_trace_id=%{NOTSPACE:log_trace_id} \| log_span_id=%{NOTSPACE:log_span_id} \| log_resource.service.name=%{DATA:log_resource.service.name} \| log_trace_sampled=%{NOTSPACE:log_trace_sampled} \| log_msg=%{GREEDYDATA:log_msg}

source.@value:
pipeline "osparc-simcore replace pipeline"
stage 0 match either
rule "replace \\n with \n for message"
stage 1 match either
rule "replace \\n with \n for log_msg"
end

description.@value: Make common values (e.g. LOG LEVEL) follow the same format (e.g. upper case)

source.@value:
pipeline "Standardize common values"
stage 0 match pass
rule "uppercase log level"
end

description.@value: Make common values (e.g. LOG LEVEL) follow the same format (e.g. upper case)

source.@value:
pipeline "Standardize common values"
stage 0 match pass
rule "uppercase log level"

pipeline "osparc-simcore replace pipeline"
stage 0 match either
rule "replace \\n with \n for message"
stage 1 match either
rule "replace \\n with \n for log_msg"
end

description.@value: replace new line char for log_msg

source.@value:
rule "replace \\n with \n for log_msg"
when
  has_field("log_msg")
then
  let newMessage = replace(to_string($message.log_msg), "\\n", "\n");
  set_field("log_msg", newMessage);
end

description.@value: replace new line char for message

source.@value:
rule "replace \\n with \n for message"
when
  has_field("message")
then
  let newMessage = replace(to_string($message.message), "\\n", "\n");
  set_field("message", newMessage);
end

description.@value: Uppercase log level to have the same format

source.@value:
rule "uppercase log level"
when
  has_field("log_level")
then
  let upper_case_level = uppercase(to_string($message.log_level));
  set_field("log_level", upper_case_level);
end
